# Content and configuration boundaries

- Store landing content in centralized files, not scattered across components.
- Keep unknown client information as explicit placeholders, for example `TODO: confirm certification`.
- Do not invent contact details, certifications, partners, client references, legal details, results, or statistics.
- Make optional sections easy to hide when the client has not provided proof yet.
- Keep content structures typed so missing required fields are caught early.
- Separate content from presentation: components render data, content files define text and values.
- Use clear keys and labels that make future client edits easy.
- Avoid coupling layout behavior to exact sentence length.
